title: Bissell Versus Cordless Bare Floor Vacuum
transcripts:
Bissell® Versus Cordless Bare Floor Vacuum and Replacement Filter

This cordless, bagless vacuum features brushless V shape technology that captures and suctions dirt for the most complete  Bissell Versus Cordless Bare Floor Vacuumclean. The shape of the base has been designed for optimal cleaning performance, forcing all of the large debris into the center suction path. The V shape also translates to better pick up of the fine debris. The angle of the arm increases air flow, allowing for greater suction at the end points of the base. The Bissell Versus works well on a variety of surfaces from bare floor to low pile carpeting. Its unique design makes it ideal for quickly cleaning messes all around the house. It has the convenience of cordless operation with up to 20 minutes of cleaning per power charge. Features a dirt container with a release pedal and a low-profile base to fit under cabinets and furniture. Measures approximately 10 2/3" W x 8 3/4" D x 43 1/2" H. UL listed. One-year limited warranty. Model # 21R9A.

The Bissell® Versus Cordless Bare Floor Vacuum is a quick and easy way to clean your bare floors and low pile area rugs without the hassle of a cord.

Designed for optimal cleaning performance, the Versus innovative V-shape forces large debris into the center suction path, while the arms capture particles.

Dirt and debris have a tendency to get under edges of baseboard and in corners, but Versus brushless arms allow for edge-to-edge cleaning along baseboards, in tight spaces, and in hard to reach corners.  And the V-shape allows for easy cleaning around furniture legs, so you never need a broom and dustpan.

The dirt cup is easy to remove and empty, so there are no bags to buy or change.  And for maximum convenience, the Versus is rechargeable for up to 20 minutes of cordless cleaning.

The Bissell Versus Cordless Bare Floor Vacuum, brushless, V-shaped technology for the most complete clean.
